00:21.800 --> 00:25.640
Reading by Simon Wainwright.

00:26.840 --> 00:34.820
The First Epistle of Paul to the Corinthians, King James Version, Chapter 3.

00:35.440 --> 00:45.440
And I, brethren, could not speak unto you as unto spiritual, but as unto carnal, even as unto babes in Christ.

00:46.020 --> 01:00.300
I have fed you with milk and not with meat, for heather too ye were not able to bear it, neither yet now are ye able, for ye are yet carnal.

01:00.780 --> 01:10.040
For whereas there is among you envying and strife and divisions, are ye not carnal and walk as men?

01:10.040 --> 01:18.740
For while one sayeth, I am of Paul, and another, I am of Apollos, are ye not carnal?

01:19.360 --> 01:25.880
Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers by whom ye believed?

01:26.620 --> 01:35.900
Even as the Lord gave to every man, I have planted, Apollos watered, but God gave the increase.

01:36.400 --> 01:44.540
So then, neither is he that planteth anything, neither he that watereth, but God that giveth the increase.

01:45.080 --> 01:59.140
Now, he that planteth and he that watereth are one, and every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labor, for we are laborers together with God.

01:59.140 --> 02:04.020
Ye are God's husbandry, ye are God's building.

02:04.720 --> 02:15.620
According to the grace of God which is given unto me as a wise master builder, I have laid the foundation, and another buildeth thereon.

02:15.980 --> 02:29.120
But let every man take heed how he buildeth thereupon, for other foundation can no man lay than that is laid which is Jesus Christ.

02:29.140 --> 02:44.320
Now, if any man build upon this foundation gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, stubble, every man's work shall be made manifest, for the day shall declare it,

02:44.920 --> 02:54.340
because it shall be revealed by fire, and the fire shall try every man's work of what sort it is.

02:54.340 --> 03:01.540
If any man's work abide which he hath built thereupon, he shall receive a reward.

03:02.140 --> 03:12.600
If any man's work shall be burned, he shall suffer loss, but he himself shall be saved, yet so as by fire.

03:13.320 --> 03:20.280
Know ye not that ye are the temple of God, and that the Spirit of God dwelleth in you?

03:20.900 --> 03:29.040
If any man defile the temple of God, him shall God destroy, for the temple of God is holy.

03:29.500 --> 03:33.660
Which temple ye are? Let no man deceive himself.

03:33.660 --> 03:44.240
If any man among you seemeth to be wise in this world, let him become a fool, that he may be wise.

03:45.000 --> 03:55.040
For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God, for it is written, he taketh the wise in their own craftiness.

03:55.460 --> 04:03.120
And again the Lord knoweth the thoughts of the wise, that they are vain. Therefore let no man

04:03.120 --> 04:12.620
glory in men, for all things are yours, whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life,

04:12.780 --> 04:23.080
or death, or things present, or things to come. All are yours, and ye are Christ's, and Christ is God.

04:25.400 --> 04:34.420
Let a man sow account of us, as of the ministers of Christ, and stewards of the mysteries of God.

04:34.800 --> 04:44.240
Moreover, it is required in stewards that a man be found faithful. But with me it is a very small thing,

04:44.700 --> 04:51.540
that I should be judged of you, or of man's judgment, yea, I judge not mine own self.

04:52.040 --> 05:03.540
For I know nothing by myself, yet am I not hereby justified, but he that judges me is the Lord.

05:04.100 --> 05:12.460
Therefore judge nothing before the time, until the Lord come, who both will bring to light

05:12.460 --> 05:17.800
the hidden things of darkness, and will make manifest

05:18.420 --> 05:24.940
the counsels of the hearts, and then shall every man have praise of God.

05:25.100 --> 05:32.960
And these things, brethren, I have in a figure, transferred to myself and to Apollos,

05:33.080 --> 05:40.520
for your sakes, that ye might learn in us not to think of men above that which is written,

05:41.100 --> 05:47.280
that no one of you be puffed up for one against another.

05:48.260 --> 05:55.560
For who maketh thee to differ from another, and what hast thou that thou dost not receive?

05:56.080 --> 06:04.980
Now, if thou dost receive it, why dost thou glory, as if thou hast not received it?

06:04.980 --> 06:15.040
Now ye are full, now ye are rich, ye have reigned as kings. Without us, and I would to God,

06:15.400 --> 06:24.680
ye did reign, that we also might reign with you. For I think that God have set forth us,

06:24.840 --> 06:33.540
the apostles, last as it were appointed to death. For we are made a spectacle unto the world,

06:33.540 --> 06:41.700
and to angels, and to men. We are fools for Christ's sake, but ye are wise in Christ.

06:42.060 --> 06:49.680
We are weak, but ye are strong. Ye are honorable, but we are despised.

06:50.220 --> 06:58.300
Even unto this present hour, we both hunger, and thirst, and are naked, and are buffeted,

06:58.300 --> 07:05.920
and have no certain dwelling place, and labor, working with our own hands.

07:06.540 --> 07:15.060
Being reviled, we bless. Being persecuted, we suffer it. Being defamed, we entreat.

07:15.800 --> 07:23.940
We are made as the filth of the world, and are the offscouring of all things unto this day.

07:23.940 --> 07:30.940
I write not these things to shame you, but as my beloved sons I warn you.

07:31.820 --> 07:39.240
For though ye have ten thousand instructors in Christ, yet have ye not many fathers.

07:39.740 --> 07:45.640
For in Christ Jesus, I have begotten you through the gospel.

07:46.480 --> 07:53.720
Wherefore I beseech you, be ye followers of me. For this cause have I sent unto you,

07:53.940 --> 08:01.400
Timotheus, who is my beloved son, and faithful in the Lord, who shall bring you

08:01.400 --> 08:10.460
into remembrance of my ways which be in Christ, as I teach everywhere in every church.

08:10.860 --> 08:18.080
Now some are puffed up as though I would not come to you, but I will come to you shortly,

08:18.080 --> 08:26.760
if the Lord will, and will know not the speech of them which are puffed up, but the power.

08:27.100 --> 08:35.630
For the kingdom of God is not in word, but in power. What will ye? Shall I come unto you with

08:35.630 --> 08:41.730
or in love, and in the spirit of meekness?

